    • Constructor Detail

      • InstrumentUpdateInfo

        public InstrumentUpdateInfo(IInstrument instrument,
                            boolean usePriceDecimals,
                            InstrumentComponentTagsConfig instrumentComponentConfig,
                            IFIXMessageFactory factory,
                            boolean fast)
        Create an InstrumentUpdateInfo based on the given instrument.

        If usePriceDecimals is true, prices are treated as if they have the number of implied decimal places as defined by the instrument's IInstrument.getImpliedPriceDecimalPlaces() method.

        If groupIDTag is greater than zero, it is the FIX tag number of the tag used to define the group ID associated with this instrument.

        Parameters:
        instrument - Associated instrument
        usePriceDecimals - True if a price's implied decimal places are to be taken into account when populating price fields in a message.
        instrumentComponentConfig - Instrument configuration.
        factory - The message factory to be used for creating messages. If null, defaults to DefaultToFIXMessageFactory.
        fast - True if FAST compression is being used.

      • getTopOfBookRequestedFieldIDs

        public int[] getTopOfBookRequestedFieldIDs()
        Description copied from interface: IInstrumentUpdateInfo
        Returns all requested FieldID's, grouped by their corresponding MDEntryTypes.

        Note that it is important that all FieldID's for a given MDEntryType are together in the array. The populateTopOfBookMessage method in MarketDataProcessor depends on this - otherwise field values may not appear under the correct MDEntryType entry in a FIX message.

        This is computed from the requested MDEntryTypes (as returned by IInstrumentUpdateInfo.getTopOfBookRequestedMDEntryTypes() when the entryTypes are first requested.

        Specified by:
        getTopOfBookRequestedFieldIDs in interface IInstrumentUpdateInfo
        Returns:
        FieldID's matching the requested MDEntryTypes.

      • setInstrumentDefinition

        public void setInstrumentDefinition(List tagValues)
        Defines the fields required to define this instrument in the form of a List of ITagValue.

        The default instrument definition consists of a single pair where tag = Constants.TAGiSymbol (55) and the string is the symbol (as defined by IInstrument.getSymbol()).

        Calling this method is optional.

        Parameters:
        tagValues - List of ITagValue's defining the instrument.

      • setTempDepthSubscription

        public void setTempDepthSubscription(boolean tempSubscription)
        Used to record the fact that a temporary subscription has been made.

        Normally subscriptions are made in response to a explicit subscription request from the FIX counterparty and communicated to this object through one of the processXXX methods.

        However, sometimes it is necessary to subscribe temporarily. For example, if a snapshot request is received but we have no defined data and are not currently subscribed, then it is necessary to subscribe once to get some good data which can be used to satisfy the snapshot request, then we can unsubscribe.

        This method does not perform any subscriptions. It just records the fact that a temporary subscription has been made. The value of this attribute will affect the corresponding isXXXSubscribed method.

        Parameters:
        tempSubscription - True if a temporary subscription has been made.
